MPC

Class TypeProcFunc

  • java.lang.Object
    • MPC.ASTNode
      • MPC.Type
        • MPC.TypeProcFunc

  • public class TypeProcFunc
extends Type
    Representation of a (MiniObject-)Pascal procedure/function signature, containing formal parameters, result type, and binding (name). While the binding is not strictly necessary, it is convenient for identification when printing, etc.

    • Field Detail

      • formals

        public final Decls formals
        Declaration list of formal parameters. Note that methods must have at least one formal parameter, which formal designates the invocant or target of the method and must be the first formal and be of a type compatible with the object type in which this method is defined (in practice, these will always be the same type, as it makes no sense for the formal to be a supertype.

      • resultType

        public Type resultType
        the Type of the result of this method (null if method is procedural)

                    Decls formals,
                    Type resultType,
                    int left,

        Creates a new TypeProcFunc given its binding, formals, result type and source (start/end) position.
        Parameters:
        binding - Binding corresponding to the method name as exposed by the TypeObject
        formals - Decls of the formal parameters to the method (used only for the types)
        resultType - Type of the result value (if any; specify null for a procedure
        left - starting position in program text
        right - ending position in program text
